title: "The Invisible Arrangement"
type: atom
tags:
  - metaphor
  - knowledge-management
---

Same utensils, new kitchen layout. I know I will be opening the wrong drawer for a knife for weeks because the muscle memory doesn't transfer.

The stuff moves easily. It's the invisible arrangement that made everything feel effortless. That's what I have to rebuild.

This is why decoupling context from model matters. The invisible arrangement (how things are organised, indexed, and retrieved) is the real intellectual capital. Owning it means I control how the new model finds the knife.
